    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for various earthy materials containing silica, alumina, and iron oxides; often contains compounds of barium or calcium. Occurs in yellowish, brown, or reddish colors.Ochers are also used as pigment, colorants in ceramic slips and glazes, added as a reducing agent in luster glazes, and as a filler in linoleum and other products. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
